	<content><![CDATA[const yesNo = (val, def = false) =>
  /^(y|yes)\$/i.test(val) ? true : /^(n|no)\$/i.test(val) ? false : def;]]></content>
	<description>Returns `true` if the string is `y`/`yes` or `false` if the string is `n`/`no`.  Use `RegExp.test()` to check if the string evaluates to `y/yes` or `n/no`. Omit the second argument, `def` to set the default answer as `no`.</description>
